        "_account_id": 793,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "adegremont@nvidia.com",
        "username": "degremoa"
      },
      "date": "2019-01-29 10:49:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThere is no good reasons for this to be done that way indeed.\n\nThis was probably done that way to call to mdt_agent_record_update() only once and also because it was never thought that there would be that many pending requests.\n\nThis problem was seen with 2.10.5. Patches from LU-10383 makes really hard to be in a so bad state, as the candidate list will be smaller (and we are now using OBD_ALLOC_LARGE instead of OBD_ALLOC in 2.10)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
